WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.679 --> 00:00:02.311
Previously on The Following...

2
00:00:02.675 --> 00:00:05.716
Serial killer Joe Carroll
has escaped from prison.

3
00:00:05.851 --> 00:00:07.051
Get some help now!

4
00:00:07.164 --> 00:00:09.213
Ryan. I know
things didn't end well with the Bureau.

5
00:00:09.327 --> 00:00:10.435
but you caught Carroll.

6
00:00:10.537 --> 00:00:11.662
No one knows him like you do.

7
00:00:11.751 --> 00:00:12.865
I'm not an agent anymore.

8
00:00:12.977 --> 00:00:14.493
He cut out his victims' eyes as a nod

9
00:00:14.618 --> 00:00:15.966
to his favorite works of Poe.

10
00:00:16.072 --> 00:00:18.013
He didn't just
eviscerate 14 female students.

11
00:00:18.123 --> 00:00:19.051
He was making art.

12
00:00:19.176 --> 00:00:20.581
Sarah was his unfinished work.

13
00:00:20.678 --> 00:00:21.840
He wanted to get the ending right.

14
00:00:21.953 --> 00:00:24.992
The point of Sarah's death was for you.

15
00:00:25.101 --> 00:00:26.139
He's finding people.

16
00:00:26.252 --> 00:00:27.405
They're his followers.

17
00:00:27.514 --> 00:00:28.853
Prison guard.
gay neighbors--

18
00:00:28.957 --> 00:00:30.913
how do they figure into your new plot?

19
00:00:31.011 --> 00:00:31.939
We know about the cult.

20
00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:33.978
I like to think of them as my friends.

21
00:00:34.070 --> 00:00:35.502
So what's my sequel about. Joe?

22
00:00:35.604 --> 00:00:37.019
We're gonna write this together. Ryan.

23
00:00:37.126 --> 00:00:39.430
even though you slept with my wife.

24
00:00:39.527 --> 00:00:40.528
Did she show you the letter?

25
00:00:40.635 --> 00:00:41.645
- How does he know?
- He doesn't.

26
00:00:41.758 --> 00:00:42.725
No one need to know about this.

27
00:00:42.836 --> 00:00:44.798
- Mom. what's going on?
- Yeah.

28
00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:46.049
It's dad. isn't it?

29
00:00:46.158 --> 00:00:47.751
- I didn't know what to say.
- Oh. honey.

30
00:00:47.875 --> 00:00:49.725
If this book ends with
anything other than your death.

31
00:00:49.837 --> 00:00:51.527
you better plan on a rewrite.

32
00:00:51.668 --> 00:00:52.871
Aah! Aah!

33
00:00:52.969 --> 00:00:53.934
Joey? Where is he?

34
00:00:54.036 --> 00:00:55.936
Joey! Joey. honey.
where are you?

35
00:00:56.042 --> 00:00:58.144
Where's Denise?
Where's my son?!

36
00:00:59.355 --> 00:01:01.101
Sorry. Didn't mean
to scare you.

37
00:01:01.351 --> 00:01:02.873
Is everything ok?

38
00:01:02.973 --> 00:01:04.289
Extra patrol this evening.

39
00:01:04.411 --> 00:01:05.609
I thought they caught him.

40
00:01:05.703 --> 00:01:06.674
I saw it on the news.

41
00:01:06.808 --> 00:01:07.712
Still. mind if I look around.

42
00:01:07.814 --> 00:01:08.857
check your doors and windows?

43
00:01:08.963 --> 00:01:10.194
Sure.

44
00:01:12.525 --> 00:01:13.717
Come on in.

45
00:01:14.043 --> 00:01:15.803
I think everyone's asleep.

46
00:01:16.142 --> 00:01:18.434
_

47
00:01:18.541 --> 00:01:20.269
Why don't we start upstairs?

48
00:01:25.499 --> 00:01:26.761
Do you want me to wake everyone?

49
00:01:26.894 --> 00:01:28.710
No. We don't want
to do that.

50
00:01:28.812 --> 00:01:31.055
Let's start with the room on the end.

51
00:01:31.293 --> 00:01:32.558
Ok.

52
00:01:39.758 --> 00:01:41.933
This is Jesse's room. She's out.

53
00:01:42.037 --> 00:01:45.246
Yes. Jesse's room.
I know.

54
00:01:47.406 --> 00:01:49.246
I've studied this house a lot.

55
00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:57.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

56
00:02:00.731 --> 00:02:02.190
What is that?

57
00:02:02.999 --> 00:02:05.117
I threw this up here earlier.

58
00:02:05.988 --> 00:02:07.586
It's my kit.

59
00:02:08.108 --> 00:02:11.304
It's important to have the right tools.

60
00:02:14.487 --> 00:02:16.908
I've been planning
this for a long time.

61
00:02:18.515 --> 00:02:21.385
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

62
00:02:23.104 --> 00:02:25.375
Convicted serial killer Joe Carroll

63
00:02:25.498 --> 00:02:27.171
has been captured and is being held

64
00:02:27.278 --> 00:02:29.373
at the Richmond
Federal Detention Center.

65
00:02:29.527 --> 00:02:32.388
As of early this morning.
Carroll's son Joey Matthews

66
00:02:32.511 --> 00:02:34.930
and his nanny Denise Harris
have been missing.

67
00:02:35.096 --> 00:02:36.780
An amber alert is in effect.

68
00:02:36.904 --> 00:02:39.862
and we ask that anyone
with any information

69
00:02:39.986 --> 00:02:43.023
as to their whereabouts
please contact the FBI.

70
00:02:43.132 --> 00:02:45.246
What's going on. Ryan?
Where is my son?

71
00:02:45.377 --> 00:02:46.537
We need to talk.

72
00:02:46.641 --> 00:02:48.306
Why is Joe doing this?

73
00:02:48.447 --> 00:02:49.922
I don't understand how
Denise is involved.

74
00:02:50.018 --> 00:02:51.367
Are they gonna hurt Joey?

75
00:02:52.187 --> 00:02:54.577
I think she's your nanny
because of Joe.

76
00:02:54.683 --> 00:02:55.494
I think he put
her here--

77
00:02:55.599 --> 00:02:56.798
No. That's
impossible.

78
00:02:56.983 --> 00:02:58.963
She's been Joey's nanny for two years.

79
00:02:59.087 --> 00:03:00.560
She lives with me. I know her.

80
00:03:01.122 --> 00:03:04.193
The accomplices. the guys that
helped him kill Sarah Fuller.

81
00:03:04.302 --> 00:03:05.459
they were there for years.

82
00:03:05.640 --> 00:03:06.761
using false identities.

83
00:03:06.891 --> 00:03:08.144
We think that she did. too.

84
00:03:08.254 --> 00:03:09.887
I did a background check.

85
00:03:10.010 --> 00:03:12.051
I checked her references.
I have records.

86
00:03:12.167 --> 00:03:13.139
Can I see them?

87
00:03:13.253 --> 00:03:14.483
Yeah.

88
00:03:19.331 --> 00:03:21.681
Heavy traces of Zolpidem
on the kitchen counter.

89
00:03:21.824 --> 00:03:22.747
She drugged the guards.

90
00:03:22.863 --> 00:03:23.937
I bet the kid. too.

91
00:03:24.042 --> 00:03:25.875
Carried him down the back
staircase to the garage.

92
00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:27.160
Car was found 10 minutes ago

93
00:03:27.284 --> 00:03:29.100
in a parking lot 45 minutes from here.

94
00:03:35.318 --> 00:03:37.098
Denise Harris from Alexandria.

95
00:03:37.210 --> 00:03:39.702
Her address. her references.
it's all there.

96
00:03:40.035 --> 00:03:41.428
She talked about her mom a lot.

97
00:03:41.586 --> 00:03:42.919
I guess they were close.

98
00:03:43.088 --> 00:03:44.048
No dad in the picture.

99
00:03:44.172 --> 00:03:45.281
You ever meet any of her friends

100
00:03:45.397 --> 00:03:46.754
or overhear a phone conversation?

101
00:03:46.877 --> 00:03:48.643
Her friends never came over.
She was shy.

102
00:03:48.807 --> 00:03:50.117
she kept to herself.

103
00:03:50.649 --> 00:03:53.364
She read in her room a lot.

104
00:03:55.344 --> 00:03:57.027
I can't be this blind. can I?

105
00:03:57.158 --> 00:03:59.865
You cannot afford to think
like that. do you understand?

106
00:04:01.733 --> 00:04:03.290
Find my son.

107
00:04:15.923 --> 00:04:17.572
Hey! You can't
run from me!

108
00:04:22.211 --> 00:04:24.908
Ha ha ha! Whee!

109
00:04:25.132 --> 00:04:26.339
Err!

110
00:04:27.105 --> 00:04:28.856
I got you!

111
00:04:30.735 --> 00:04:32.048
Look at this place.

112
00:04:39.182 --> 00:04:40.618
Wow!

113
00:04:41.043 --> 00:04:42.365
Whose house is this?

114
00:04:42.496 --> 00:04:43.517
Friend of a friend.

115
00:04:43.638 --> 00:04:44.861
And it's ok that we're here?

116
00:04:44.966 --> 00:04:48.111
Yeah. Come on!
Let's check it out!

117
00:04:50.163 --> 00:04:51.885
Can I call my mom now?

118
00:04:52.001 --> 00:04:55.350
Honey. I told you.

119
00:04:55.718 --> 00:04:57.786
Your mom told us not to call.

120
00:04:57.926 --> 00:05:00.008
She doesn't want anyone
to know where we are.

121
00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:02.345
You remember what I said?

122
00:05:02.458 --> 00:05:03.669
We're on an adventure!

123
00:05:03.775 --> 00:05:05.977
Mm-hmm. Come here.

124
00:05:08.749 --> 00:05:09.869
What's wrong with you?

125
00:05:09.977 --> 00:05:11.403
- I hate kids.
- Stop it.

126
00:05:11.488 --> 00:05:12.489
I do. I hate
talking to them.

127
00:05:12.601 --> 00:05:13.394
I hate looking at them.

128
00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:15.380
Hey. Not
this kid. ok?

129
00:05:15.593 --> 00:05:17.249
You like this kid.

130
00:05:17.686 --> 00:05:20.223
Just keep saying it over and
over again until it sticks.

131
00:05:20.324 --> 00:05:21.613
I'd rather snap his neck.

132
00:05:24.398 --> 00:05:25.793
I'm kidding.

133
00:05:30.545 --> 00:05:31.444
Is there a problem?

134
00:05:31.566 --> 00:05:33.109
Nope. No. Not here.

135
00:05:33.258 --> 00:05:34.926
We're on an adventure with a kid.

136
00:05:35.187 --> 00:05:38.197
and I like kids. especially this kid.

137
00:05:44.461 --> 00:05:45.655
What was that about?

138
00:05:46.564 --> 00:05:50.026
It's been a long night. he's tired.

139
00:05:58.555 --> 00:06:00.284
It's good to have you back.

140
00:06:00.862 --> 00:06:03.000
_

141
00:06:03.115 --> 00:06:04.914
More developments
from Richmond. Virginia.

142
00:06:05.035 --> 00:06:06.854
upon Sarah Fuller's death as the search

143
00:06:06.979 --> 00:06:09.014
for young Joey Matthews continues.

144
00:06:09.156 --> 00:06:11.147
Convicted serial killer
Joe Carroll's son

145
00:06:11.254 --> 00:06:12.650
is believed to have been abducted...

146
00:06:12.752 --> 00:06:14.571
Ok. The team over there's
covering the ground search.

147
00:06:14.743 --> 00:06:16.469
that group is
on our prison guard Jordy.

148
00:06:16.578 --> 00:06:18.173
and we've got Joey's search right here.

149
00:06:18.598 --> 00:06:20.952
Ryan Hardy. this is Agent
Mitchell. Cyberforensics.

150
00:06:21.082 --> 00:06:22.770
She's from our DC office.
She's awesome.

151
00:06:22.917 --> 00:06:24.006
Nice to meet you. sir.

152
00:06:24.114 --> 00:06:25.164
Where are we are on the nanny?

153
00:06:25.285 --> 00:06:26.695
I know Denise Harris
is not from Alexandria

154
00:06:26.823 --> 00:06:28.797
because Denise Harris does not exist.

155
00:06:28.902 --> 00:06:31.870
But we IDed Sarah Fuller's
gay or not-so-gay neighbors.

156
00:06:31.983 --> 00:06:34.177
Real names are Jacob Wells
and Paul Torres.

157
00:06:34.325 --> 00:06:35.506
Jacob is from Lake Whitehurst.

158
00:06:35.628 --> 00:06:37.013
Paul is form El Paso. Texas.

159
00:06:37.121 --> 00:06:38.896
Where he's a computer consultant
with a history of fraud.

160
00:06:38.988 --> 00:06:40.661
which explains all the fake IDs.

161
00:06:40.783 --> 00:06:42.104
Where's Agent Mason?

162
00:06:50.184 --> 00:06:52.207
I'd just get rid of him. send him home.

163
00:06:52.584 --> 00:06:54.552
You can't. You heard Carroll.
He's part of the story.

164
00:06:54.665 --> 00:06:56.080
Then sideline him before he cracks

165
00:06:56.197 --> 00:06:57.360
because he will crack.

166
00:06:57.472 --> 00:07:00.125
You weren't around
10 years ago. I lived... it.

167
00:07:04.181 --> 00:07:06.982
Well. this is awkward.

168
00:07:07.721 --> 00:07:08.815
Hello. Mr. Hardy.

169
00:07:08.942 --> 00:07:09.934
I'm Agent Debra Parker.

170
00:07:10.041 --> 00:07:11.395
I'm new the party.

171
00:07:11.518 --> 00:07:14.885
We were just. uh. discussing you.

172
00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:17.478
Agent Parker's in from Quantico.
She's taking the lead.

173
00:07:17.575 --> 00:07:18.721
I want to speak to
Mr. Hardy privately.

174
00:07:18.813 --> 00:07:19.666
Where's Mason?

175
00:07:19.772 --> 00:07:21.173
She's on her way back to Quantico.

176
00:07:21.359 --> 00:07:23.693
Apparently she put a former agent alone

177
00:07:23.791 --> 00:07:24.848
in a room with Joe Carroll

178
00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:26.474
and let him break 3 of his fingers.

179
00:07:26.735 --> 00:07:28.704
Turns out
that's a no-no.

180
00:07:29.110 --> 00:07:29.894
3. huh?

181
00:07:30.022 --> 00:07:31.829
Marshal Turner thinks
I should dismiss you.

182
00:07:31.972 --> 00:07:33.699
but he's remembering you for
the man you were 10 years ago.

183
00:07:33.801 --> 00:07:34.867
not the man you are now.

184
00:07:35.019 --> 00:07:36.002
And there's a difference?

185
00:07:36.125 --> 00:07:38.187
I hope so because Joe Carroll

186
00:07:38.299 --> 00:07:40.441
has cast you as the main
character in his psycho sequel.

187
00:07:40.553 --> 00:07:42.458
so I can't just kick you to the curb.

188
00:07:45.151 --> 00:07:47.163
I'm sorry about Sarah Fuller.

189
00:07:48.597 --> 00:07:50.163
I want a gun.

190
00:07:50.305 --> 00:07:51.594
I'm not asking to be an agent again.

191
00:07:51.697 --> 00:07:53.802
but you need to deputize me
and give me a gun.

192
00:07:53.915 --> 00:07:55.511
When was the last time you had a drink?

193
00:07:56.058 --> 00:07:58.213
Director Franklin asked me to be here.

194
00:07:58.337 --> 00:08:00.136
and if I'm gonna stay. I want a gun.

195
00:08:00.248 --> 00:08:01.409
I'll take it under advisement.

196
00:08:01.511 --> 00:08:02.851
How's your heart?
I see here you suffer

197
00:08:02.956 --> 00:08:04.421
from. uh. cardiomyopathy.

198
00:08:04.533 --> 00:08:06.616
Is this really
the best use of our time?

199
00:08:06.729 --> 00:08:07.595
There's a child missing.

200
00:08:07.711 --> 00:08:09.247
So tell me about Carroll's accomplices.

201
00:08:13.358 --> 00:08:16.339
He used this prison guard to
gain access to the internet

202
00:08:16.456 --> 00:08:18.530
to create a following. like a cult.

203
00:08:18.635 --> 00:08:20.389
Let's not use that word.
People don't hear it well.

204
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:21.660
Well. you can call it what you want.

205
00:08:21.768 --> 00:08:23.391
but he solicited people
to do his bidding.

206
00:08:23.497 --> 00:08:25.535
Carroll mentioned a letter?

207
00:08:31.384 --> 00:08:35.222
Claire Matthews received a letter
about a week before Carroll's escape.

208
00:08:35.337 --> 00:08:36.718
It was personal.

209
00:08:38.292 --> 00:08:40.137
He questioned my relationship with her.

210
00:08:40.242 --> 00:08:42.381
As did the FBI 8 years ago.

211
00:08:43.781 --> 00:08:45.853
So now you're up to speed.

212
00:08:47.582 --> 00:08:49.029
We got more bodies.

213
00:08:51.766 --> 00:08:54.110
Blood smear.
Jordy was messy.

214
00:08:54.246 --> 00:08:55.542
Left prints everywhere.

215
00:08:55.644 --> 00:08:57.828
Made no attempt
to conceal his identity.

216
00:08:57.947 --> 00:09:01.785
Victim number 3-- she tried
to run. quick struggle.

217
00:09:01.895 --> 00:09:03.507
Not the case for the others.

218
00:09:09.271 --> 00:09:11.210
There were 9 girls
in the house at the time.

219
00:09:11.328 --> 00:09:12.847
Some of them woke up when
they heard the screams.

220
00:09:12.963 --> 00:09:14.945
and Jordy ran.

221
00:09:15.039 --> 00:09:17.050
He removed the eyes--
Carroll's signature.

222
00:09:17.167 --> 00:09:18.785
Is Jordy playing
at Poe's greatest hits?

223
00:09:18.899 --> 00:09:20.126
It's paying homage to Carroll.

224
00:09:20.227 --> 00:09:22.500
It's following in the
footsteps of his hero.

225
00:09:22.611 --> 00:09:25.083
it's ceremonial.
the work of an acolyte.

226
00:09:25.182 --> 00:09:26.693
Let's not use that word either.

227
00:09:26.810 --> 00:09:28.063
It implies the other word.

228
00:09:28.158 --> 00:09:29.725
Let's say.
"Carroll's accomplices."

229
00:09:29.827 --> 00:09:34.231
Pick a word. any word. but
this is mind control at work.

230
00:09:34.353 --> 00:09:35.391
Why have his son kidnapped?

231
00:09:35.488 --> 00:09:36.992
It's an offering. it's biblical.

232
00:09:37.099 --> 00:09:38.661
They think of him as the son of God.

233
00:09:38.782 --> 00:09:41.233
something to be worshiped.

234
00:09:41.347 --> 00:09:42.900
Or sacrificed.

235
00:09:43.365 --> 00:09:44.992
Carroll knows where the kid is.

236
00:09:45.092 --> 00:09:46.079
He's not gonna tell us.

237
00:09:46.210 --> 00:09:48.414
But he might tell his wife.

238
00:09:48.944 --> 00:09:50.172
Carroll asked to see her.

239
00:09:50.275 --> 00:09:52.481
He's smarter than that.
He's not gonna tell her anything.

240
00:09:52.599 --> 00:09:54.237
Well. let's find out.

241
00:09:58.598 --> 00:10:00.215
What do I say?

242
00:10:00.996 --> 00:10:02.641
Is there anything special
I need to ask him?

243
00:10:02.835 --> 00:10:04.818
Try to engage him about Joey.

244
00:10:05.610 --> 00:10:07.758
speak to his paternal instincts.

245
00:10:07.865 --> 00:10:09.642
Make Joey important to him.

246
00:10:12.770 --> 00:10:14.526
Are you sure you want to do this?

247
00:10:34.765 --> 00:10:36.356
I like your new place.

248
00:10:36.486 --> 00:10:37.972
Me. too.

249
00:10:38.427 --> 00:10:39.801
How was court today?

250
00:10:39.910 --> 00:10:41.645
Moving fast.
Won't be long now.

251
00:10:41.748 --> 00:10:44.248
I can't go anymore.
I can't look at him.

252
00:10:46.545 --> 00:10:48.660
I don't ever want to see him again.

253
00:10:50.672 --> 00:10:52.570
You don't have to.

254
00:11:32.268 --> 00:11:34.082
My hands are shaking.

255
00:11:34.479 --> 00:11:37.268
My God.
You still have that effect on me.

256
00:11:37.545 --> 00:11:38.829
You're so beautiful
always--

257
00:11:38.946 --> 00:11:40.457
Where's my son?

258
00:11:42.961 --> 00:11:44.657
Our son. Claire.

259
00:11:44.766 --> 00:11:48.367
Please. Joe.
Where is he?

260
00:11:49.814 --> 00:11:52.415
Do you remember when
we went to Antigua.

261
00:11:53.293 --> 00:11:56.790
we rented that little
cottage on the beach?

262
00:11:56.898 --> 00:11:58.596
We were only supposed to
be there for a few days.

263
00:11:58.739 --> 00:12:00.213
but it turned into a whole month.

264
00:12:00.338 --> 00:12:02.503
I don't think we wore
clothes the entire time.

265
00:12:02.599 --> 00:12:05.255
He's growing up
so fast-- Joey is.

266
00:12:05.383 --> 00:12:08.886
He's so brilliant. reading
well beyond his years--

267
00:12:09.010 --> 00:12:10.239
Melville and Twain.

268
00:12:10.352 --> 00:12:11.796
He finished "Robinson
Crusoe" last week.

269
00:12:11.922 --> 00:12:12.971
but he didn't like it very much.

270
00:12:13.091 --> 00:12:14.782
It must be so hard for you.

271
00:12:15.750 --> 00:12:18.003
You must feel so betrayed.

272
00:12:19.787 --> 00:12:21.226
Again.

273
00:12:22.986 --> 00:12:25.951
Come on. Claire.
Hang in there.

274
00:12:29.978 --> 00:12:32.536
So you...
got my letter.

275
00:12:32.676 --> 00:12:34.194
Is he in danger. Joe?

276
00:12:35.652 --> 00:12:37.105
Please just let him be. ok. ok?

277
00:12:37.213 --> 00:12:38.070
Please don't let him be hurt.

278
00:12:38.181 --> 00:12:40.376
I'd like some answers to my questions.

279
00:12:47.922 --> 00:12:49.121
Tell me where Joey is first.

280
00:12:49.245 --> 00:12:52.524
I asked you some very
specific questions.

281
00:12:52.636 --> 00:12:53.766
I'd like you to answer them.

282
00:12:53.875 --> 00:12:56.673
- Yes.
- "Yes." you what?

283
00:12:59.707 --> 00:13:03.194
Ryan and I had an affair
for almost two months.

284
00:13:06.780 --> 00:13:08.205
After the trial?

285
00:13:08.380 --> 00:13:09.407
And the divorce.

286
00:13:09.515 --> 00:13:10.952
Oh. yes. Of course.

287
00:13:11.068 --> 00:13:13.369
You waited for the divorce.

288
00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:17.078
Noble Claire.
Only a proper little diddle will do.

289
00:13:17.892 --> 00:13:21.247
Was it good. the sex?

290
00:13:21.358 --> 00:13:24.433
Did you body quiver to his every touch?

291
00:13:27.469 --> 00:13:29.176
Yes.

292
00:13:29.806 --> 00:13:31.186
It did.

293
00:13:31.336 --> 00:13:32.426
We got to get her out of there.

294
00:13:32.531 --> 00:13:33.810
Not yet.

295
00:13:34.895 --> 00:13:36.031
And the last question?

296
00:13:36.145 --> 00:13:37.306
- I don't know.
- Oh. you know the question.

297
00:13:37.423 --> 00:13:40.661
I don't know is my answer.

298
00:13:41.948 --> 00:13:43.668
How could I love anyone after you?

299
00:13:43.777 --> 00:13:46.380
You destroyed me.
You son of a bitch!

300
00:13:46.491 --> 00:13:48.945
Where's my son?
Where is Joey. you bastard?

301
00:13:49.053 --> 00:13:51.428
Where is--
ohh! Aah!

302
00:13:51.526 --> 00:13:52.698
We need to get
in there. Damn it!

303
00:13:52.818 --> 00:13:55.033
I will always love you.

304
00:13:57.965 --> 00:13:59.442
No! Off!

305
00:14:15.635 --> 00:14:16.838
You ok?

306
00:14:16.962 --> 00:14:18.103
Yes.

307
00:14:18.659 --> 00:14:20.354
I'm sorry about what I said in there.

308
00:14:20.973 --> 00:14:23.161
Don't be. Got a car
waiting to take--

309
00:14:23.280 --> 00:14:24.753
Is there any news on Joey?

310
00:14:26.605 --> 00:14:29.073
As soon as I know anything.
I promise--

311
00:14:30.279 --> 00:14:31.885
we're gonna find him. Claire.

312
00:14:40.458 --> 00:14:41.935
Which room do I get?

313
00:14:42.059 --> 00:14:43.691
I don't know.
Let's see.

314
00:14:46.148 --> 00:14:49.353
Whoa! It's just like
my room at home!

315
00:14:49.462 --> 00:14:51.279
My ninja warrior!

316
00:14:51.574 --> 00:14:52.930
And it's brand-new!

317
00:14:53.049 --> 00:14:54.124
How cool is that?

318
00:14:54.276 --> 00:14:55.721
Supercool!

319
00:14:56.071 --> 00:14:57.619
Can I call mom now?

320
00:14:57.733 --> 00:15:01.325
Honey. she asked us not to call.

321
00:15:01.638 --> 00:15:03.146
We have to wait.

322
00:15:03.262 --> 00:15:05.681
Why is my dad such a bad man?

323
00:15:07.608 --> 00:15:09.543
Oh. honey.

324
00:15:11.552 --> 00:15:12.641
Come here.

325
00:15:17.041 --> 00:15:21.565
Maybe he's not so bad.

326
00:15:22.373 --> 00:15:25.026
Maybe we just don't understand him.

327
00:15:27.110 --> 00:15:29.989
I'll tell you what.
why don't you get settled

328
00:15:30.132 --> 00:15:32.496
and check out all your new things?

329
00:15:36.274 --> 00:15:38.983
"Good and bad no longer existed.

330
00:15:39.552 --> 00:15:42.324
It was all degrees of evil now.

331
00:15:42.783 --> 00:15:45.358
Gwendolyn held his dying body

332
00:15:45.735 --> 00:15:49.183
as the storm raged on.

333
00:15:49.339 --> 00:15:51.589
Death had finally arrived.

334
00:15:52.356 --> 00:15:56.746
and it was glorious
to the touch."

335
00:16:02.604 --> 00:16:04.736
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

336
00:16:08.462 --> 00:16:10.440
Thank you for coming. uh...

337
00:16:10.808 --> 00:16:14.102
Emma. I loved
your book.

338
00:16:14.217 --> 00:16:16.227
So you're the one. Emma.

339
00:16:17.565 --> 00:16:21.018
It's beautiful.
All the imagery's so vivid.

340
00:16:21.124 --> 00:16:23.085
I felt like I was there.

341
00:16:23.237 --> 00:16:26.489
Oh. You just
made my day.

342
00:16:27.499 --> 00:16:29.940
Uh. may I just. uh--

343
00:16:33.803 --> 00:16:36.076
you have such lovely eyes. Emma.

344
00:16:36.204 --> 00:16:37.645
Don't deprive us of them.

345
00:16:42.341 --> 00:16:44.627
Did she die--
Gwendolyn-- at the end

346
00:16:44.727 --> 00:16:47.557
when she went into the sea and
started swimming to the horizon?

347
00:16:47.668 --> 00:16:49.307
Well. you tell me.

348
00:16:49.913 --> 00:16:51.676
I think she died.

349
00:16:51.825 --> 00:16:56.391
She was swimming toward the
horizon. toward the Sun.

350
00:16:57.710 --> 00:17:00.169
In death. she found hope.

351
00:17:01.423 --> 00:17:03.558
Emma. hon.
You almost done?

352
00:17:03.659 --> 00:17:05.322
- I'm ready. mom--
- Oh.

353
00:17:05.435 --> 00:17:07.922
So this is the fella you came to see.

354
00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:11.263
My. my. I thought all writers
were big-nosed and mushy.

355
00:17:11.390 --> 00:17:13.128
- Not you.
- Mom. please. Let's go.

356
00:17:13.249 --> 00:17:15.161
I'm giving the man a compliment.

357
00:17:15.264 --> 00:17:17.024
No. sir. You do not
look like a writer.

358
00:17:17.196 --> 00:17:18.743
Did he sign your book?

359
00:17:18.867 --> 00:17:21.441
Oh. yes.
Mustn't forget this.

360
00:17:21.890 --> 00:17:29.675
"Emma. hopefully yours.
Joe."

361
00:17:35.342 --> 00:17:37.097
So which is our room?

362
00:17:44.734 --> 00:17:46.138
You mean. your room.

363
00:17:46.247 --> 00:17:48.070
Jacob and I are taking the master.

364
00:17:48.356 --> 00:17:49.575
You can't do that.

365
00:17:49.691 --> 00:17:51.275
Well. you're not gay anymore. remember?

366
00:17:51.385 --> 00:17:52.463
We were never gay.

367
00:17:52.565 --> 00:17:56.240
It's just with the kid. is that cool?

368
00:17:56.670 --> 00:17:58.164
Don't worry about it.

369
00:18:01.259 --> 00:18:02.840
I tracked her
through the prison footage.

370
00:18:02.960 --> 00:18:05.605
She used several aliases very
similar to the gay guys.

371
00:18:05.829 --> 00:18:06.965
3 years ago.

372
00:18:08.632 --> 00:18:09.866
The guy beside her.

373
00:18:09.990 --> 00:18:11.923
Jacob Wells.
You connected them.

374
00:18:12.035 --> 00:18:14.269
And get this.
I did a search for Jacob...

375
00:18:16.669 --> 00:18:18.256
Paul Torres.

376
00:18:18.455 --> 00:18:19.770
They signed in together.

377
00:18:19.882 --> 00:18:21.366
You were right.
They're all in on this.

378
00:18:21.472 --> 00:18:23.644
Hey. Find the first time
the nanny visited Carroll.

379
00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:25.502
Maybe she didn't use an alias.

380
00:18:28.246 --> 00:18:31.221
2004. she signed in as Emma Hill.

381
00:18:31.839 --> 00:18:34.606
Ok. There's an Emma Hill
in Petersburg. Virginia.

382
00:18:34.738 --> 00:18:35.671
I have an address.

383
00:18:35.785 --> 00:18:37.962
Petersburg is too close.
They'd never risk it.

384
00:18:38.071 --> 00:18:39.713
Unless they're hiding under our nose.

385
00:18:40.497 --> 00:18:42.653
Go. Take Weston.

386
00:18:43.309 --> 00:18:44.702
And Ryan.

387
00:18:46.169 --> 00:18:48.487
Call ahead. Have the local
authorities meet you there.

388
00:18:48.594 --> 00:18:49.811
Ok.

389
00:18:57.887 --> 00:18:59.145
Nobody's home.

390
00:18:59.278 --> 00:19:00.413
This is definitely the place.

391
00:19:00.507 --> 00:19:02.548
Neighbors say they haven't
seen anybody in a long time.

392
00:19:04.779 --> 00:19:06.605
Ok. You can't do that.

393
00:19:06.701 --> 00:19:08.818
Nope. You can't
do that.

394
00:19:09.140 --> 00:19:09.976
I'm gonna go check around back.

395
00:19:10.072 --> 00:19:11.779
see if I can see through the window.

396
00:21:11.683 --> 00:21:13.075
You shouldn't be here.

397
00:21:13.533 --> 00:21:15.177
You know. you're gonna die.

398
00:21:15.289 --> 00:21:16.468
Only not today.

399
00:21:16.681 --> 00:21:17.636
Unh!

400
00:21:24.727 --> 00:21:26.955
Good news--
no dead puppies.

401
00:21:27.650 --> 00:21:30.038
Bad news-- I think it's
time to use that word

402
00:21:30.157 --> 00:21:31.458
nobody wants to use.

403
00:21:31.579 --> 00:21:34.681
So we have a cult.

404
00:21:35.178 --> 00:21:36.837
You sure this man wasn't Jordy?

405
00:21:36.923 --> 00:21:39.398
Height. weight-- nothing matched.
It was someone else.

406
00:21:39.507 --> 00:21:41.154
We weren't supposed to find this place.

407
00:21:41.359 --> 00:21:43.157
This is where they met and planned.

408
00:21:43.257 --> 00:21:44.013
I think Carroll was--

409
00:21:44.111 --> 00:21:47.744
Carroll's using Poe's
work as a religion.

410
00:21:47.846 --> 00:21:50.338
He's speaking to people
through Gothic Romanticism.

411
00:21:50.444 --> 00:21:55.183
There's a pathology to today's
internet techno-bred minds.

412
00:21:55.607 --> 00:21:58.846
It's created a new...
vacancy in our humanity.

413
00:21:59.931 --> 00:22:04.512
Find the ones with additional
disorders-- jackpot.

414
00:22:04.789 --> 00:22:08.331
Enter a handsome. charismatic man

415
00:22:08.616 --> 00:22:10.269
who can touch them.

416
00:22:11.426 --> 00:22:14.466
let them feel their lives
for the first time.

417
00:22:14.780 --> 00:22:16.390
conditions them.

418
00:22:17.866 --> 00:22:22.549
The only way to truly live is to kill.

419
00:22:24.010 --> 00:22:26.304
Or some crap like that.

420
00:22:28.935 --> 00:22:31.548
I run the Bureau's
alternative religion unit.

421
00:22:31.680 --> 00:22:33.271
Did I not mention that?

422
00:22:33.537 --> 00:22:36.377
Cults-- my specialty.

423
00:22:42.359 --> 00:22:43.411
Hey.
We online?

424
00:22:43.525 --> 00:22:44.879
- Yeah.
- Is it secure?

425
00:22:44.985 --> 00:22:46.974
It's a little slow. but I got
us keyed into the board.

426
00:22:47.087 --> 00:22:48.489
It's untraceable.

427
00:22:48.599 --> 00:22:49.819
You check the news yet?

428
00:22:49.938 --> 00:22:51.536
Yeah. We're everywhere. man.

429
00:22:52.466 --> 00:22:54.815
That's the photo that they pick of me?

430
00:22:54.926 --> 00:22:56.088
I hate that picture.

431
00:22:56.197 --> 00:22:58.173
Did you get it running?
What's up with Jordy?

432
00:22:58.279 --> 00:22:59.269
Well. he hasn't
e-mailed yet.

433
00:22:59.369 --> 00:23:01.540
but they did find 3 girls
at the sorority house.

434
00:23:01.669 --> 00:23:03.488
Score for the village idiot.

435
00:23:04.495 --> 00:23:06.702
Hey. Paul. Will you go watch
Joey for a few minutes?

436
00:23:06.806 --> 00:23:08.061
I can do it.

437
00:23:09.947 --> 00:23:11.753
Be a good wingman. Paul.

438
00:23:20.770 --> 00:23:22.639
Are you sure he's straight?

439
00:23:22.794 --> 00:23:24.956
Because he is acting like
a jealous little bitch.

440
00:23:25.851 --> 00:23:28.158
He just feels like the third wheel.

441
00:23:28.843 --> 00:23:31.429
And for a long time.
it was just me and him.

442
00:23:31.544 --> 00:23:32.861
Now everything's changed.

443
00:23:32.960 --> 00:23:34.845
Well. he needs to adjust.

444
00:23:36.797 --> 00:23:38.923
This is what Joe wanted.

445
00:23:41.299 --> 00:23:42.968
What do you think?

446
00:23:44.137 --> 00:23:46.758
My mom says that it
makes me look like a boy

447
00:23:48.152 --> 00:23:49.978
or a girl who doesn't like boys.

448
00:23:50.096 --> 00:23:51.554
Well. your mother
doesn't understand you.

449
00:23:51.654 --> 00:23:53.025
She never has.

450
00:23:53.786 --> 00:23:57.009
No. I like it
very much. Emma.

451
00:23:57.138 --> 00:23:58.718
It's beautiful.

452
00:24:00.817 --> 00:24:04.114
What if I told you that I might know

453
00:24:04.246 --> 00:24:06.867
someone else who might like it. too?

454
00:24:09.018 --> 00:24:10.471
A guy?

455
00:24:11.085 --> 00:24:13.087
You want to set me up?

456
00:24:14.085 --> 00:24:16.415
I think you'd like each other.

457
00:24:16.842 --> 00:24:18.730
I don't know.

458
00:24:21.733 --> 00:24:23.915
I love our visits.

459
00:24:24.097 --> 00:24:25.972
They mean the world to me.

460
00:24:27.592 --> 00:24:31.425
but I think you need to
make more friends.

461
00:24:31.543 --> 00:24:35.884
you know. go out. have some fun. huh?

462
00:24:39.442 --> 00:24:41.190
Heh heh heh.

463
00:24:46.352 --> 00:24:47.975
Emma?

464
00:24:51.540 --> 00:24:53.101
Hi.

465
00:24:56.285 --> 00:24:58.301
Joe said you'd be my type.

466
00:25:00.036 --> 00:25:01.821
What's your type?

467
00:25:04.850 --> 00:25:06.679
Special.

468
00:25:21.732 --> 00:25:24.238
I've got 8. maybe 9
different handwritings.

469
00:25:24.360 --> 00:25:25.798
I want analysis on each one.

470
00:25:25.919 --> 00:25:26.574
How many prints?

471
00:25:26.673 --> 00:25:28.384
4. Clean.
Several partial.

472
00:25:28.498 --> 00:25:29.995
Our masked man was living here. too.

473
00:25:30.100 --> 00:25:31.320
Unmade bed. fresh food.

474
00:25:31.426 --> 00:25:32.434
There's internet upstairs.

475
00:25:32.548 --> 00:25:33.947
He took his laptop and server.

476
00:25:39.623 --> 00:25:42.556
_

477
00:25:44.890 --> 00:25:46.910
Is it ok if I'm happy about this?

478
00:25:47.031 --> 00:25:50.425
I mean. I know-- I know divorce is
not a happy subject.

479
00:25:50.545 --> 00:25:52.533
but I'm happy.

480
00:25:52.646 --> 00:25:54.099
Well. it's a new chapter in your life.

481
00:25:54.226 --> 00:25:57.457
I mean. you know. Joe's
been sentenced. he's gone.

482
00:25:57.728 --> 00:25:59.734
I think you deserve some happy.

483
00:26:00.447 --> 00:26:04.023
All right. Well. here's to
being a single lady again.

484
00:26:05.141 --> 00:26:06.483
Ooh.
That's depressing.

485
00:26:06.591 --> 00:26:07.705
Ha ha.

486
00:26:09.558 --> 00:26:10.887
Kiss me.

487
00:26:13.390 --> 00:26:14.622
Yeah. yeah.
You heard me.

488
00:26:14.740 --> 00:26:16.514
I'm single. so just...

489
00:26:18.363 --> 00:26:19.668
Are you sure you want me to kiss you?

490
00:26:19.776 --> 00:26:21.022
Uh. yeah.
I'm very sure.

491
00:26:21.132 --> 00:26:22.912
I've been sure for a long time.

492
00:26:23.444 --> 00:26:25.543
Well. if you're sure.

493
00:26:25.649 --> 00:26:26.882
Unless-- are-- but--

494
00:26:27.002 --> 00:26:28.392
are you sure?
Because if--

495
00:26:28.515 --> 00:26:29.649
I don't think first kisses are

496
00:26:29.809 --> 00:26:31.710
supposed to have this much discussion.

497
00:26:31.825 --> 00:26:33.219
I know. It takes the
spontaneity out of it.

498
00:26:33.345 --> 00:26:34.128
Yeah. it kind of does.

499
00:26:34.237 --> 00:26:35.706
Did I just ruin our first kiss?

500
00:26:36.357 --> 00:26:38.423
I think it can be salvaged.

501
00:27:02.965 --> 00:27:04.892
So we got an update from Rick.

502
00:27:05.907 --> 00:27:08.004
FBI found Emma's house.

503
00:27:09.065 --> 00:27:10.748
What do you mean
they found Emma's house?

504
00:27:10.863 --> 00:27:11.730
Was Jordy there?

505
00:27:11.824 --> 00:27:13.116
No. Rick was.
but he got away.

506
00:27:13.229 --> 00:27:14.868
Now he wants Emma to call.

507
00:27:15.164 --> 00:27:16.418
Why?

508
00:27:17.084 --> 00:27:19.303
Because she's in charge. remember?

509
00:27:19.448 --> 00:27:21.522
I'm not trusted with
the important things.

510
00:27:22.223 --> 00:27:24.374
That's not true. all right?

511
00:27:24.600 --> 00:27:28.015
She's just been here
for longer. that's all.

512
00:27:28.297 --> 00:27:31.187
You guys need to stop this
thing that you got going.

513
00:27:31.313 --> 00:27:32.195
It's awkward.

514
00:27:32.301 --> 00:27:34.181
Awkward for whom. man?

515
00:27:34.580 --> 00:27:37.022
Look. I'm fine.
It's just I don't get

516
00:27:37.132 --> 00:27:38.694
what you see in her.

517
00:27:39.309 --> 00:27:41.325
You're way out of her league. man.

518
00:27:44.744 --> 00:27:47.252
I think she's amazing.

519
00:27:58.470 --> 00:28:01.220
So tell me. Jacob.

520
00:28:01.772 --> 00:28:03.278
what do you do?

521
00:28:05.888 --> 00:28:08.659
Uh. currently I am in between jobs.

522
00:28:09.987 --> 00:28:12.728
Well. you're too pretty to work.

523
00:28:12.976 --> 00:28:14.142
Mom!

524
00:28:14.979 --> 00:28:16.828
I can't believe you two are dating.

525
00:28:20.063 --> 00:28:23.939
Your daughter is the most
amazing woman I know.

526
00:28:24.279 --> 00:28:26.543
Hmm. Hmm.

527
00:28:26.650 --> 00:28:28.429
So you like
the no-fuss plain Janes.

528
00:28:28.546 --> 00:28:29.586
That's sweet.

529
00:28:29.703 --> 00:28:30.983
Most boys don't.

530
00:28:31.109 --> 00:28:32.601
Unh!

531
00:28:33.328 --> 00:28:39.393
♪ I watched a change in you ♪

532
00:28:39.713 --> 00:28:46.159
♪ it's like you never had wings ♪

533
00:28:46.253 --> 00:28:47.838
You did it.

534
00:28:48.375 --> 00:28:52.652
♪ Now you feel so alive ♪

535
00:28:53.181 --> 00:28:57.818
♪ I've watched you change ♪

536
00:28:57.926 --> 00:28:59.706
You really did it.

537
00:29:00.352 --> 00:29:05.234
♪ It's like you never had wings ♪

538
00:29:05.377 --> 00:29:10.392
♪ ahh. ahh. ahh ♪

539
00:29:12.088 --> 00:29:13.911
♪ I'm home ♪

540
00:29:31.335 --> 00:29:33.021
Who are all these women?

541
00:29:33.712 --> 00:29:37.250
They're all names of women in
Poe's life and work that died.

542
00:30:06.421 --> 00:30:09.470
A female.
She's been dead a while.

543
00:30:09.593 --> 00:30:10.882
The mother?

544
00:30:11.252 --> 00:30:12.691
Buried in the wall.

545
00:30:12.807 --> 00:30:15.250
"The Black Cat."
"The Cask Of Amontillado."

546
00:30:15.388 --> 00:30:16.840
classic Poe.

547
00:30:27.622 --> 00:30:28.815
Call the Matthews residence.

548
00:30:28.934 --> 00:30:30.714
Make sure Claire Matthews is safe.

549
00:30:40.290 --> 00:30:41.811
She's safe.
The house is secure.

550
00:30:41.942 --> 00:30:43.430
There's no sign of entry.

551
00:30:48.006 --> 00:30:48.889
Anything?

552
00:30:49.030 --> 00:30:51.003
Denise's real name is Emma Hill.

553
00:30:51.154 --> 00:30:52.795
She's been visiting Joe in prison.

554
00:30:52.911 --> 00:30:56.373
She is part of this.
but. no. we didn't find her.

555
00:31:16.217 --> 00:31:18.724
Hey. fellas.
Eyes up. huh?

556
00:31:18.839 --> 00:31:23.302
You're on watch.
Coffee break for God's sake.

557
00:31:43.936 --> 00:31:45.550
All good.

558
00:32:01.035 --> 00:32:03.114
9 different handwritings were found.

559
00:32:03.343 --> 00:32:05.073
We matched all our suspects.

560
00:32:05.188 --> 00:32:08.380
but. uh. 5 remain unidentified.

561
00:32:09.340 --> 00:32:13.675
ME has confirmed that the dead body is
Emma's mother Sharon Cooper.

562
00:32:13.796 --> 00:32:15.676
Still no ID on the masked man.

563
00:32:16.524 --> 00:32:19.609
Jordy. a disorganized
killer with a low IQ.

564
00:32:19.728 --> 00:32:21.834
how does he just disappear?

565
00:33:23.081 --> 00:33:24.170
What are those?

566
00:33:24.713 --> 00:33:25.968
Blueprints.

567
00:33:27.160 --> 00:33:29.583
They were on the wall
of the nanny's house.

568
00:33:31.222 --> 00:33:33.331
That's the closet
they took her through.

569
00:33:34.728 --> 00:33:37.328
That's the garage where
the officer was killed.

570
00:33:42.283 --> 00:33:46.035
Wait a minute.
That's Claire's basement!

571
00:33:51.951 --> 00:33:53.438
Go. go. go!

572
00:33:53.552 --> 00:33:54.964
Cover the back!

573
00:33:58.287 --> 00:34:00.492
Don't shoot!
I'm unarmed.

574
00:34:00.596 --> 00:34:02.347
It's you.

575
00:34:02.592 --> 00:34:05.576
Finally. You know.
we've been waiting for you.

576
00:34:05.692 --> 00:34:08.037
Keep them out!
Keep everybody out!

577
00:34:08.139 --> 00:34:09.559
Get back!
Everyone back.

578
00:34:09.655 --> 00:34:10.971
Get back!

579
00:34:11.439 --> 00:34:12.800
Ok. Jordy.

580
00:34:14.031 --> 00:34:15.535
They're gone.

581
00:34:15.794 --> 00:34:18.588
Just us. Ok?

582
00:34:19.918 --> 00:34:21.366
Can I shut the door?

583
00:34:21.475 --> 00:34:23.334
Yeah. That's good.
You shut the door.

584
00:34:35.307 --> 00:34:36.862
Take the gun away from her head.

585
00:34:36.960 --> 00:34:38.433
I have to kill her.

586
00:34:38.634 --> 00:34:39.834
No. you don't.

587
00:34:39.995 --> 00:34:41.522
And you have to watch.

588
00:34:41.682 --> 00:34:44.880
Those are the rules.
or. uh--

589
00:34:45.478 --> 00:34:46.938
Or what?

590
00:34:47.152 --> 00:34:49.304
Or you have to kill me.

591
00:34:51.039 --> 00:34:53.135
I'm not sure I'm ready to die.

592
00:34:53.254 --> 00:34:54.429
Jordy. nobody has to die.

593
00:34:54.543 --> 00:34:55.815
Joe doesn't want her to die.

594
00:34:55.923 --> 00:34:57.258
Yes. he does!

595
00:34:57.344 --> 00:34:59.736
And he chose me to do it.
not anyone else. me!

596
00:34:59.842 --> 00:35:02.892
This is my chapter. and I can
write it any way I want to!

597
00:35:03.004 --> 00:35:04.683
Ok. I'll tell you what.

598
00:35:05.223 --> 00:35:06.647
Why don't we call him?

599
00:35:07.732 --> 00:35:10.913
We can call him.
We can ask him.

600
00:35:11.267 --> 00:35:12.707
I have his number.

601
00:35:14.930 --> 00:35:18.773
There's a phone right
over there by the bed.

602
00:35:22.493 --> 00:35:24.070
Get an ambulance!

603
00:35:32.436 --> 00:35:34.499
The storm windows were padlocked.

604
00:35:34.611 --> 00:35:35.919
The man had a key.

605
00:35:36.043 --> 00:35:37.039
The nanny gave it to him.

606
00:35:37.153 --> 00:35:38.330
He was dressed as a cop.

607
00:35:38.451 --> 00:35:39.845
He hid under one of the AC units

608
00:35:39.979 --> 00:35:41.270
nobody knew about.

609
00:35:41.413 --> 00:35:43.688
Except the nanny. who gave it to him.

610
00:35:43.805 --> 00:35:45.128
Come on.
How are we supposed to know that?

611
00:35:45.251 --> 00:35:46.760
It's your job!

612
00:35:48.598 --> 00:35:51.444
Ok. Listen up.
If you're not a federal agent.

613
00:35:51.566 --> 00:35:53.936
I want you out of this
house now. you understand?

614
00:35:54.045 --> 00:35:55.366
Come on.
Let' go.

615
00:36:22.136 --> 00:36:23.818
What's up?

616
00:36:25.031 --> 00:36:26.923
She's a strong woman.

617
00:36:27.090 --> 00:36:28.493
She has to be.

618
00:36:28.764 --> 00:36:29.986
The prison guard's in surgery.

619
00:36:30.099 --> 00:36:31.128
He'll be fine.

620
00:36:31.243 --> 00:36:32.810
We'll question him the
second he's conscious.

621
